{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"[G4 child-consistency — container review of parent 1f19-adf2-ffb2-4b09 paired with THIS child (S5 b7fa: Surface the ref + source controls on the CLI and MCP tool schemas)]\n\nRan the 7 cross-child interaction modes for this surface child against the WHOLE sibling roster (S1 6d56, S2 70c7, S3 fa49, S4 30b3, S6 1ba5). All 7 modes are clean under the high-confidence / benign-reading filter — EMPTY G4 findings list for this pairing.\n\nMode-by-mode:\n- implicit shared state: The shared values this child surfaces all have a single named producer and a consistent producer→consumer chain. `ref`/`source` params: produced as a concept by the parent's \"What\", threaded into the gate dispatch by S3 (fa49), surfaced on CLI flags + MCP tool-schema args here. `verified_at_sha`: resolved by S1, threaded by S3, recorded/signed by S4 (30b3), surfaced in attested outputSchema/text here (this child AC2), documented by S6. `origin/main` default: this child AC1/AC3 (\"--ref default origin/main\"; \"Omitting --ref resolves origin/main -> SHA\") matches S3's default and S6's documented default. No shared-state divergence.\n- conflicting assumptions: This child's surface claims agree with the behaviors siblings implement. AC3 (\"Omitting --ref resolves origin/main -> SHA (attested) and still signs (pin recorded)\") matches S4 AC1 (attested PASS records verified_at_sha + signs) and S1 (resolve ref -> immutable SHA). AC4 (\"--source=local ... reflected as unsigned\") matches S3 AC2 (local marks-unsigned) and S4 AC2 (local bars-signing). The five named tool surfaces (review_plan/verify_completion/review_ticket/review_code/scan_spec) are exactly S3's five gates. No contradiction.\n- dependency gap: Every obligation this child surfaces is implemented by a named sibling — param threading by S3 (its file_impact: completion.py/pai_tools.py/mcp_server.py), signing/verified_at_sha by S4, SHA resolution by S1, prose semantics by S6. This child's own scope (\"Out: the underlying behavior (S1-S4); prose docs (S6)\") delegates each piece to a present sibling. The standing roster dependency-gap (the pinned-SHA snapshot handle not routed into plan_review/attest.py's dependency_hashes()/_rehash()/freshness re-check) is a seam between S3 and S4; it is downstream of this surface child and does not touch the CLI/MCP schema work. No gap originated or left unowned at THIS child.\n- scope overlap: Two potential overlaps, both clean. (a) ref/source documentation: this child surfaces \"documented defaults\" inline in the schema (machine-facing outputSchema/text), while S6 owns the human PROSE (S6 AC3); S5 explicitly scopes \"prose docs (S6)\" out and S6 scopes \"code (S1-S5)\" out — a schema-text vs prose split, not double-ownership of one artifact (consistent with the S6 G4 review already on record). (b) S5 What bullet 3 (\"the MCP server no longer depends on its own cwd/branch ...; document that REBAR_ROOT only locates the object DB\") restates the re-rooting outcome S3 owns (S3 AC5: \"repo_root only locates the object DB to fetch from; the verified code is the snapshot\") — but S5 only SURFACES/documents that fact at the schema layer (its \"What\" frames it as the no-cwd-dependence note), it does not re-implement the re-rooting; S3 owns the behavior. Producer/surface split, no double-implementation.\n- ordering violation: Logical S1->S3->S4->this-child ordering with S6 documenting; all six children carry empty deps uniformly and parent AC8 only requires all-closed + green, so no encoded ordering is violated (consistent with the roster-wide posture in prior reviews).\n- consumer impact: This child is a terminal surface/consumer — it consumes S3's threaded ref/source params and S4's verified_at_sha to expose them on CLI/MCP; it produces no new behavior contract that a sibling must satisfy, so it imposes no downstream breakage.\n- residual references: review_plan/verify_completion/review_ticket/review_code/scan_spec (S3's five gates), verified_at_sha (S4), the S1-S4 underlying-behavior scope-out and S6 prose-docs scope-out, REBAR_ROOT (real env in config.py:26 / README.md:193,261), origin/main default — all resolve to real producers/siblings/symbols. No dangling reference.\n\nNote (not a G4 finding on THIS pairing): the standing dependency-gap finding on sibling S4 (30b3) about routing the pinned-SHA snapshot handle into plan_review/attest.py (dependency_hashes()/_rehash()/the ADR-0002 freshness re-check, all rooted on _config.repo_root) is a code seam between S3 and S4; it is unrelated to this CLI/MCP-surface child and out of this pairing's scope. Likewise the S1/S3 conflicting-assumptions seam (whether materialize() runs in local mode) flagged on S1 does not touch this surface child.\n\nConclusion: no high-confidence cross-child inconsistency between this surface child (S5) and the parent/siblings — the ref/source CLI+MCP surfacing and verified_at_sha exposure are a clean producer/surface split over S3's threading and S4's signing, with prose docs cleanly delegated to S6. Empty G4 findings list for this pairing."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782521255298532001,"uuid":"0a763885-0224-4875-b063-e0cbae45f7fe"}